@@ -0,0 +1,154 @@
+# Tableau MCP Server Integration
+
+This document describes the integration of the Tableau MCP (Model Context Protocol) server with the existing Tableau LangChain project.
+
+## Overview
+
+The project has been updated to use the Tableau MCP server instead of making direct VDS (VizQL Data Service) API calls. This provides several benefits:
+
+- **Standardized Integration**: Uses the MCP protocol for consistent AI tool integration
+- **Centralized Authentication**: Authentication is handled by the MCP server
+- **Simplified Deployment**: Reduces the need for direct Tableau API credentials in each application
+- **Better Error Handling**: Centralized error handling and logging
+
+## MCP Server URL
+
+The default MCP server URL is:
+```
+https://allison-mcp-server.up.railway.app/tableau-mcp
+```
+
+## Configuration
+
+### Environment Variables
+
+Set the following environment variable to configure the MCP server:
+
+```bash
+export MCP_SERVER_URL="https://allison-mcp-server.up.railway.app/tableau-mcp"
+```
+
+### Configuration Module
+
+The project includes a configuration module at `pkg/langchain_tableau/utilities/config.py` that manages MCP server settings:
+
+```python
+from langchain_tableau.utilities.config import get_mcp_server_url, set_mcp_server_url
+
+# Get current MCP server URL
+url = get_mcp_server_url()
+
+# Set a new MCP server URL
+set_mcp_server_url("https://your-mcp-server.com/tableau-mcp")
+```
+
+## Updated Components
+
+### 1. MCP Client (`pkg/langchain_tableau/utilities/mcp_client.py`)
+
+New MCP client that handles communication with the Tableau MCP server:
+
+```python
+from langchain_tableau.utilities.mcp_client import TableauMCPClient
+
+client = TableauMCPClient()
+result = client.query_datasource(datasource_luid, query)
+metadata = client.get_metadata(datasource_luid)
+```
+
+### 2. Updated VizQL Data Service (`pkg/langchain_tableau/utilities/vizql_data_service.py`)
+
+The existing `query_vds` and `query_vds_metadata` functions now use the MCP server by default:
+
+```python
+from langchain_tableau.utilities.vizql_data_service import query_vds, query_vds_metadata
+
+# These now use the MCP server automatically
+result = query_vds(api_key, datasource_luid, url, query)
+metadata = query_vds_metadata(api_key, datasource_luid, url)
+```
+
+### 3. Updated Simple Datasource QA Tools
+
+Both the main and experimental versions of `simple_datasource_qa.py` have been updated to use the MCP server:
+
+- `pkg/langchain_tableau/tools/simple_datasource_qa.py`
+- `experimental/tools/simple_datasource_qa.py`
+
+## Backward Compatibility
+
+The integration maintains backward compatibility:
+
+- All existing function signatures remain the same
+- The `api_key` and `url` parameters are kept for compatibility but not used with MCP
+- Legacy direct VDS functions are available as `query_vds_direct` and `query_vds_metadata_direct`
+
+## Migration Guide
+
+### For Existing Code
+
+No changes are required for existing code. The integration is transparent:
+
+```python
+# This code continues to work without changes
+from langchain_tableau.utilities.vizql_data_service import query_vds
+
+result = query_vds(
+    api_key="your-api-key",
+    datasource_luid="your-datasource-luid",
+    url="https://your-tableau-server.com",
+    query={"fields": [{"fieldCaption": "Sales"}]}
+)
+```
+
+### For New Code
+
+New code can optionally use the MCP client directly:
+
+```python
+from langchain_tableau.utilities.mcp_client import TableauMCPClient
+
+client = TableauMCPClient()
+result = client.query_datasource("datasource-luid", {"fields": [{"fieldCaption": "Sales"}]})
+```
+
+## Error Handling
+
+The MCP integration includes improved error handling:
+
+- Network connectivity issues are properly reported
+- MCP server errors are clearly identified
+- Fallback to direct VDS calls is available if needed
+
+## Testing
+
+The integration has been tested and verified to work correctly. The MCP client can:
+
+- Initialize successfully
+- Communicate with the MCP server
+- Handle errors gracefully
+- Maintain compatibility with existing code
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+### Common Issues
+
+1. **404 Errors**: Ensure the MCP server URL is correct and the server is running
+2. **Authentication Errors**: Verify that the MCP server has proper Tableau credentials
+3. **Network Errors**: Check network connectivity to the MCP server
+
+### Debug Mode
+
+Enable debug logging to troubleshoot issues:
+
+```python
+import logging
+logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)
+```
+
+## Future Enhancements
+
+- Support for additional MCP server endpoints
+- Enhanced error reporting and retry logic
+- Configuration validation and health checks
+- Performance monitoring and metrics
